<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<PcGts xmlns="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15 http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15/pagecontent.xsd"><Metadata><Creator>xl-export</Creator><Created>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</Created><LastChange>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</LastChange></Metadata><Page imageFilename="" imageWidth="1000" imageHeight="1000"><TextRegion id="r1" custom="type:paragraph"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,1000 0,1000" /><TextLine id="l1" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,31 0,31" /><Baseline points="0,29 1000,29" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He said: "The thing where no one will know. Where five</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l2" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,31 1000,31 1000,62 0,62" /><Baseline points="0,60 1000,60" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>hundred people read Augustine tomorrow and not one of them</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l3" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,62 1000,62 1000,93 0,93" /><Baseline points="0,91 1000,91" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>will know that a man spent six months with this text, that</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l4" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,93 1000,93 1000,124 0,124" /><Baseline points="0,122 1000,122" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>the man wept at a particular sentence, that the sentence</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l5" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,124 1000,124 1000,155 0,155" /><Baseline points="0,153 1000,153" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>changed the man, that the man's changed hand copied it with</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l6" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,155 1000,155 1000,186 0,186" /><Baseline points="0,184 1000,184" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>a different pressure than the lines before and after, that a</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l7" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,186 1000,186 1000,217 0,217" /><Baseline points="0,215 1000,215" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>reader in Bruges in 1280 noticed the pressure changing and</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l8" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,217 1000,217 1000,248 0,248" /><Baseline points="0,246 1000,246" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>slowed down because of it, and that slowing-down was its own</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l9" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,248 1000,248 1000,279 0,279" /><Baseline points="0,277 1000,277" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>kind of reading that is not possible tomorrow. You know that</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l10" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,279 1000,279 1000,310 0,310" /><Baseline points="0,308 1000,308" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>is ending. You have known since you first came here."</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l11" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,310 1000,310 1000,341 0,341" /><Baseline points="0,339 1000,339" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He was not cruel when he said it. He was the way he always</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l12" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,341 1000,341 1000,372 0,372" /><Baseline points="0,370 1000,370" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>is, which is exact.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l13" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,372 1000,372 1000,403 0,403" /><Baseline points="0,401 1000,401" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I said: "You find that acceptable."</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l14" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,403 1000,403 1000,434 0,434" /><Baseline points="0,432 1000,432" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He said: "I find it true. There is a library in</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l15" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,434 1000,434 1000,465 0,465" /><Baseline points="0,463 1000,463" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Constantinople that is ash. I watched it. I watched it for</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l16" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,465 1000,465 1000,496 0,496" /><Baseline points="0,494 1000,494" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>two days. When it was finished I thought: the books that</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l17" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,496 1000,496 1000,527 0,527" /><Baseline points="0,525 1000,525" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>survived survived because there were too many copies to</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l18" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,527 1000,527 1000,558 0,558" /><Baseline points="0,556 1000,556" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>burn. Every copy that ever felt like a diminishment — every</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l19" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,558 1000,558 1000,589 0,589" /><Baseline points="0,587 1000,587" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>reader who winced at a scribe's error, every scholar who</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l20" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,589 1000,589 1000,620 0,620" /><Baseline points="0,618 1000,618" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>mourned the distance from the original, every man like you</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l21" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,620 1000,620 1000,651 0,651" /><Baseline points="0,649 1000,649" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>who grieved the copy's imperfection — every one of them was</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l22" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,651 1000,651 1000,682 0,682" /><Baseline points="0,680 1000,680" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>a root by which the living text clung to the earth despite</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l23" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,682 1000,682 1000,713 0,713" /><Baseline points="0,711 1000,711" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>what men do to cities." He paused. "I would like there to be</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l24" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,713 1000,713 1000,744 0,744" /><Baseline points="0,742 1000,742" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>too many copies to burn. That is my theology."</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l25" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,744 1000,744 1000,775 0,775" /><Baseline points="0,773 1000,773" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I had no answer.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l26" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,775 1000,775 1000,806 0,806" /><Baseline points="0,804 1000,804" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I have been looking for one ever since.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l27" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,806 1000,806 1000,837 0,837" /><Baseline points="0,835 1000,835" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Later, at Hartmann's — Demetrios told me, over wine, in his</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l28" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,837 1000,837 1000,868 0,868" /><Baseline points="0,866 1000,866" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>precise way — he said: "The Church condemnation exists</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l29" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,868 1000,868 1000,899 0,899" /><Baseline points="0,897 1000,897" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>because of exactly this. Not because Eckhart was wrong.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l30" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,899 1000,899 1000,930 0,930" /><Baseline points="0,928 1000,928" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Because the transmission was ungoverned. Every copyist a</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l31" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,930 1000,930 1000,961 0,961" /><Baseline points="0,959 1000,959" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>theologian. Every scriptorium a council. The press ends</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l32" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,961 1000,961 1000,992 0,992" /><Baseline points="0,990 1000,990" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>that. One authoritative edition. One text. The scholars</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine></TextRegion></Page></PcGts>